Package Search

Class Search

java.lang.Object
Search.Search
public class Search extends Object
Class to search csv file given item as a string to search for, user can provide column name, index, or none to search entire file.

  • Constructor Details

    • Search

      public Search(String fileName, boolean hasHeader) throws FactoryFailureException, IOException
      Constructor to build a Search object to begin searching in target csv file. May search with given column name, column index number, or no column specification. Create Parse object to read-in csv file and convert each row to a list of object.
      Parameters:
      fileName - file path under data directory (data/ (fill in))
      hasHeader - true if csv has header, false otherwise
      Throws:
      FactoryFailureException - when parser fails to convert each row into List of string object
      IOException - when invalid file name or file not found

  • Method Details

    • checkStringEqual

      public boolean checkStringEqual(String a, String b)
      Compares string a to b after trimming and replacing all whitespaces. Capitalization are viewed as different strings. (Used in Search to see if item an is the same as item b).
      Parameters:
      a - string a
      b - string b
      Returns:
      true if string an is equal to string b, false otherwise

    • printFoundRow

      public void printFoundRow(List<String> row, String searchFor, String columnName, int colIndex, boolean found)
      Print out the row in given csv that contains the item we're looking for according to column identification specifications. When row not found, not found messages are printed instead according to given column identification.
      Parameters:
      row - item found in this row, null if item not found
      searchFor - item to search for
      columnName - name of the column item was found if provided column name, null if no column name specified
      colIndex - the index of column item was found if provided column index, -1 if no column index specified
      found - true if item was found, false otherwise

    • makeSearchable

      public List<List<String>> makeSearchable(List<List<String>> listOfRows, List<String> headerList)
      To exclude mismatch rows based on row sizes when searching for item. If header is provided, standard row size is determined by size of list holding header items. If header not provided, standard size is determined by the first row in csv. Ensures search functions search withing index boundary.
      Parameters:
      listOfRows - containing main body csv rows (exclude header if header provided, entire csv if no header)
      headerList - if not empty (csv has header), all rows must be header size (set as standard size) to be considered as matched row in search
      Returns:
      the filtered list of main body csv rows with matching size ready for search

    • startSearch

      public List<List<String>> startSearch(String searchFor, int columnIndex) throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
      A search function to look for target item in csv given an index for the column to search under. Print out result to user interface (See printFoundRow() in Search class).
      Parameters:
      searchFor - item to look for
      columnIndex - index of column to search under
      Returns:
      list holding rows found with item under this provided column given column index
      Throws:
      ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if index provided is out of bound for csv file

    • startSearch

      public List<List<String>> startSearch(String searchFor, String columnName)
      A search function to look for target item in csv given a name for the column to search. Print out result to user interface (See printFoundRow() in Search class). Search will only happen if header row exists and if given column name is found in header list.
      Parameters:
      searchFor - item to search for
      columnName - name of column to search in this column only
      Returns:
      list holding rows found with item under this provided column name

    • startSearch

      public List<List<String>> startSearch(String searchFor)
      A search function to look through each row of csv file for item without column identifications. Print out result to user interface (See printFoundRow() in Search class).
      Parameters:
      searchFor - item to search for in entire csv file
      Returns:
      list holding rows found with item
